TOKYO, Japan, March 22, 2022/APO Group/ --
                                                        
                            The Government of Japan will hold TICAD Ministerial Meeting online on March 26 and 27. Mr. HAYASHI Yoshimasa, Minister for Foreign Affairs of Japan, will chair the meeting.



The participants including Foreign Ministers from African countries will discuss priority issues for African development looking ahead to the post-COVID-19 era based on the three pillars; Economy, Society, and Peace and Stability. The participants will also reaffirm the cooperation between Japan and African countries towards the TICAD 8.